					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=732274&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610180198" alt="thedeadlymoose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=732274)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;" >thedeadlymoose</a></span> <span class="odate time_1357124069 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Jan 2013 10:54</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1676038">
									

<p>I actually really don't like this, despite the instinctive affections I have for relics.</p>
<p>And this <em>is</em> just a relic: not really up to par. It's kind of wanky and Iceberg's character creeping hard on Rights and Break isn't all that awesome; the point of the story appears to be that Iceberg is creepy and <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">kinda</span> <em>very</em> misogynist. It's not that we can't have creepy, misogynist characters, it's just that's all there is to this story. It's not enough. The main thing I like about this is the title and that doesn't really match the rest of the story.</p>
<p>Iceberg's character is more interesting and sympathetic when written by Troy.</p>
<p>Downvoting, but I'd vote for -ARC out of affection for old dead things.</p>

							</div>

								
